  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will test a new MRI sequence that measures cerebral blood flow (CBF). Because this
      technique for measuring CBF is new, there is little information on what the normal values for
      different regions of the brain should be. Information from the study will be used to
      establish normative CBF values for the brain, improving the reliable use of this technique
      for the diagnosis of brain injury or disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
